reviews.headline: Not for sensitive skin!
reviews.comments: I received a sample jar of this with an order. The pros are that it feels really nice. It is light and not greasy. After using it for about 2 weeks, I noticed a red irritated spot on the outer corner of my eye. I didn't connect it to this immediately but put Aquafor around my eyes for a couple days till it was calmed down. I used it again and when I woke up the rod spot was back even worse and I had 2 irritated spots around my other eye. I gave it to my daughter and let her know it irritated my skin but maybe would work for them. Within 2 days, she also had red spots where it was applied.

reviews.headline: Estee Lauder Products are amazing
reviews.comments: I have been using this product for years...........Im glad Ulta has it in stock. I wish they would have the Estee Lauder perfumes too!

reviews.headline: Yes, I will continue to buy and use this product.
reviews.comments: Love, Est√©e Lauder products.

reviews.headline: Saw results fast!
reviews.comments: I recently started getting back into skincare after about   3-4 years now. After noticing my undereyes needed a loooooot of attention and love I purchased this eye gel as well as other items from this line, the soothing serum, night repair serum and the tatcha water gel. Pair together my skin already looks noticeably different and my hyperpigmentation around my eyes is significantly reduced just after 3 days of working this into my routine!! I kid you not!! The puffiness! Gone! The one thing i cannot give you an in depth review on is the wrinkle aspect. Ive put my eyes through it so its going to take a lot more than a week for me to see results on that üòÖ

reviews.headline: Have been buying this product about a year--love it!
reviews.comments: Love it! I've tried quite a few and this one is the best.  Have also been using Lancome--does not do the trick by itself but together I love them.   Don't know how long I can buy each one of them because the price doubles, but for now I will.

reviews.headline: Love it!!!!
reviews.comments: My eyes look more hydrated

reviews.headline: Buyer Beware
reviews.comments: This product severely irritated my under-eye area, leaving it red, swollen, and extremely uncomfortable. I've never experienced a reaction like this before. It burned upon application and caused significant puffiness that lasted for hours. I'm genuinely shocked and disappointed in this product.

reviews.headline: Happy I didn't spend money on this
reviews.comments: I received this as a gift and used it twice. First tome  I woke up with red irritated eyes and second time, I immediately felt my eyes burning. I had to wash it off immediately!

reviews.headline: I regret purchasing this eye cream -burning my skin
reviews.comments: I purchased this cream a few weeks ago and noticed under my eyes that my skin was red and burning.  I spent so much on this eye cream and now I can't use it.  Very disappointed!!

reviews.headline: OMG!!!!!
reviews.comments: I recently started using this. although I have used most all their other products for skin and makeup I had never tried this. It literally feels like satin when you are putting it on. So refreshing. Another 100% will buy again.

reviews.headline: Horrible, caused my eyes to water and burn
reviews.comments: So, I was very much looking forward to using this to help with the dark circles under my eyes. I bought it as a part of a travel set. The rest of the set is great so far, but this one product in it might just be the worst thing I have done to my skin. My eyes burn, they are constantly watering, and I only used it 3 times. Clearly, there is something in it that is irritating and my skin is not at all compatible with. And the sad part is I placed an order on another site to get a larger serum and they offered free samples and this was one of the offerings, and I ordered two. Because I wasn't interested in the other options. So now, I will have 4 little tubs of this stuff that I can't even use. What a waste of money!

reviews.headline: Extreme reaction
reviews.comments: I purchased this product to help with dark circles and fine lines. I used a very tiny amount of product under eyes and felt some burning. I figured it just took some time to adjust to the new product. By day 3, it felt as if I were applying acid under my eyes. I had to wash off. My eyes have a red, painful and itchy rash with puffy and wrinkly skin. Almost like a sunburn. My eyes appear to have drastically aged. The skin under my eye is now discolored. My 9-year-old has commented about how dark my eyes are now. I have had to apply ointment daily to heal. Dark circles are 10x worse. Still recovering after a week of not using. I hope my skin returns to normal soon. I typically do not have reactions to makeup or skin care. This was my first time trying this product. I will not use again.

reviews.headline: Chemical Burn
reviews.comments: I got a free sample of this with my foundation and I was so excited to try it because I love Estee Lauder. BUT, I got awful chemical burns all around my eyes. A week later and they are still pretty sore and red.

reviews.headline: Horrible
reviews.comments: Do not buy this unless you want to look like this

reviews.headline: Caused burning/itching/dry patch
reviews.comments: It seems like many users have been experiencing the same issues with this product! After using I woke up with my under eyes red and swollen with an itchy burning sensation. After a few days it has turned into a dry patch ! This is a waste of money and went straight into the trash can. Buyers beware!

reviews.headline: Burns/Rashes
reviews.comments: I was so excited to try this and loved it upon first application but it after a few uses i got these horrible rashes/burns under my eyes. I never have issues with skin sensitivty so i was shocked. Its so painful and has ruined my skin right before a big event. Very disappointed and will be returning.

reviews.headline: High price to ruin your skin.
reviews.comments: I used this eye cream years ago it USED to be amazing stopped cuz the price. Decided to give it a go again worst decision ever. First night my eyes stung a bit, the next day eyes looked slightly darker. I used to the creme 2nd night and the next day my whole under eye area was visibly darker, it's supposed to brighten under eyes but instead it makes the problem worse. It darkened areas I don't even have that problem on, all after 2 uses! I have no idea what they did but this formula is complete garbage now. Obviously I'm not dumb enough to use a 3rd time & definitely returning. I hope this review saves someone's skin and their money. Judging from other reviews this is not an isolated problem.

reviews.headline: Ow
reviews.comments: Recieved as a gift and my under eyes burned so bad the second night I used it. Zero stars!

reviews.headline: Bad Reaction
reviews.comments: I wouldn't say I have  sensitive skin or anything, but after using this product for ~3weeks, the creases of my eyes and some of my undereye developed a red, scaly almost burned like texture.

reviews.headline: Tiny!
reviews.comments: Beware the travel size is SMALL. It almost looks like a sample size rather than a true mini.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I'll be honest. I've tried my fair share of eye creams and most of them felt like expensive moisturizers in tiny jars. But the Est√©e Lauder Advanced Night Repair Eye Supercharged Gel Creme actually made me do a double take.

First impressions. The texture is dreamy. It's not too thick or greasy. Just this silky cooling gel that melts into the skin. I started using it every night before bed and even occasionally under makeup in the morning since it doesn't pill or feel heavy.

I noticed the first changes after about ten days. The constant puffiness I wake up with was gone. My under-eyes looked more awake and the crepey skin that usually makes concealer bunch up was way smoother. I didn't believe in the whole brightening dark circles claim but I swear mine have faded slightly. Not gone completely but enough that I feel okay without concealer on most days.

Also a little goes a long way. I've been using the same jar for two months now and I'm not even halfway through.

The only downside is that it's not cheap. But compared to other high-end products I've tried this one actually does something. It's a small luxury that's turned into a must-have in my routine.
faceoff_positive.headline: A little goes a long way

faceoff_negative.comments: Let me start by saying I DO NOT HAVE SENSITIVE SKIN. Next id like to say this is the worst undereye creme i have ever tried and the most pricey one iv purchased. I started using this undereye creme a few months back. and just after a couple of uses i noticed that my undereye was very dry and flakey... i thought hmm maybe i just need more moisturizing... than that dry and flakey turned into a burning sensation with a rash... that eventually turned my undereyes darker with more creasing. I had started using this to begin with as a preventative measure as i just turned 30... i did NOTTTT have dark undereyes. i stopped using it thinking maybe i just need a break... maybe its because i use it in the AM and i eventually put makeup on... ( creme is fully dried before i use my makeup) I waited a few weeks before trying it again ONLY AT NIGHT... that way there wasnt too many chemicals mixing... this last time i used it was the last time ill ever use it... I instantly felt a burning sensation as i applied it.. i used a cold cotton pad to remove it. but i woke up with the worst swelling and skin rash (almost like blisters) iv ever endured... I had to get on a steroid medication to calm it.. a week worth of pills over undereye creme. I WOULD NEVER RECOMMEND THIS PRODUCT... I WOULD NOT WISH THIS PAIN ON MY ENEMY. I WISH I COULD RETURN IT... BUT ITS WAY PAST THE DEADLINE. NEVER AGAIN.
